File: brew.info, Node: Menu function keys, Next: Menu Demos, Prev: Compile time options, Up: Users manual

Configuring function key bindings.
==================================

Here you configure function key bindings.
You reach this menu by pressing `K' in brews main screen.

Function keys are active in brews main screen and a few other places.
(Generally activating it could possibly confuse brew in some situations.

If function keys don't work on your system try toggling `use-ekey'.
This might help.

The menu lets you associate each function key with an action.
Function key bindings are active in this menu, so you can try out the result.
You can select amongst the following functions:

   * `noop'. Do nothing.

   * `context-help'. Show the manual node corresponding to the
     context.

   * `show-key-bindings'. Show active key bindings as pressing `k'
     would. *Note Example key bindings::.

   * `|feed-world|'. Feed the world an extra food portion. *Note Food
     menu::.

   * `nuc-scan-menu'. Gather statistical informations about all nucs.
     *Note Scanning nucs::.

   * `spot-scan-menu'. Gather statistical informations about all
     spots. *Note Scanning spots::.

   * `menu-step-display'. Configure brews main screens display when in
     step display. *Note Step display menu::.

   * `menu-nuc-subsets'. Do something on all nucs meeting a certain
     condition. *Note Menu nuc subsets::.

   * `menu-select-nucs'. Select or de-select nuc subsets. *Note Menu
     select nucs::.

   * `menu-current-genomes'. Examine different currently living
     genomes. *Note Menu current genomes::.

   * `food-menu'. Configure food supply. *Note Food menu::.

   * `menu-population-control'. Configure population control. *Note
     Population control::.

   * `diversification-menu'. Configure global and nuc/spot local
     variable diversifications. *Note Diversification menu::.

   * `color-menu'. Configure colors in brews main screen. *Note Color
     menu::.

   * `mutation-menu'. Configure mutation. *Note Mutation menu::.

   * `big-bang-menu'. Create a new world. *Note Big Bang menu::.

   * `world-list-menu'. Select world from worlds list. *Note World
     list menu::.

   * `world-menu'. Configure world wide options. *Note World menu::.

   * `actual-pool-menu'. Configure actual gene pool. *Note Actual pool
     menu::.

   * `gene-pool-menu'. Select gene pool. *Note Gene pools menu::.

   * `individuals-menu'. Select and edit predefined individuals to
     release in the world. *Note Individuals menu::.

   * `toggle-display-&-go'. Switch display type in brews main screen
     without stopping evolution. (Same as the `t' does). *Note Display
     modes::.

   * `do-FORTH'. Enter Forth program source and interpret it. *Note
     Using Forth in menus::.

   * `toggle-anything'. Toggle a flag variable called `anything',
     which you can use as you like. `anything' is not used by brew
     itself.

   * `function-key-menu'. Go to this menu.

   * `display-menu'. Configure display of brews main screen. *Note
     Display menu::.

   * `code-file-menu'. Configure writing generated code to a file.
     *Note Code file menu::.

   * `rec/play-menu'. Record your interactions with brew or replay
     your session. *Note Record and Playback::.

   * `log-menu'. Configure writing log files. *Note Log files menu::.

   * `system-menu'. Configure system wide options. *Note System
     menu::.

   * `menus-menu'. Go to brews super menu. *Note Menus menu::.

   * `|goodbye|'. Quit brew.




