Experiments.
============

Experiments are a more advanced kind of demos.

Currently there are only some simple test experiments, sorry.


While ordinary demos often lead you through an example evolution
`experiments' usually just initialise brew and let you run the
evolution on your own. You should have some experience with brew to
run an experiment.

Please read the source files in `INPUTS/experiments/.../' for
information what's going on in the different experiments.

In this brew version experiments are started by including an
*initialisation* file from the experiments subdirectory in
`INPUTS/experiments/'. The initialisation file will include source
files for the experiment on it's own.


*Note System menu::, for how to include files.




