File: brew.info, Node: Configuration files, Next: Output files, Prev: Genes files, Up: Files

Initialisation and configuration
--------------------------------

Technically there is a big difference between compile time
configuration and run time configuration.

   * Compile time configurations influence the program being compiled.
     You can adapt brew to your needs compiling it at your liking for
     the experiment you want to make. You cannot change these options
     without quitting brew and restart it. If you miss some features
     described in this manual you probably haven't compiled them in.
     Just change compile options and they'll be there. Some features
     might slow down brew when compiled in, even if they are switched
     off at run time.

   * Run time options just give defaults to the program at startup
     that can be changed at any time.

Brew get's compiled each time at startup phase from source. The Forth
compiler is very fast, you probably won't even notice the time needed
for compilation on todays hardware and Forth systems. So the
difference between compile time options and run time options is not so
obvious at first glance.


Configuration files listed in their load sequence:

   * `compile-options.fs' Brew default compile time options as
     delivered with this brew version.

   * `my-compile-options.fs' Configuration file to put personal
     compile time options overriding defaults.


   * `brew-defaults.fs' Brew default initialisation after compilation.
     This file sets all the defaults but does not define individuals
     and does not set any into the current world. You can produce an
     alternative initialisation by configuring through the menus,
     saving it and copy the resulting file here or to a later
     configuration file.

   * `brew-init.fs' After the general defaults have been set, this
     file defines individuals and sets some into the current world.
     You can produce an alternative initialisation and copy the
     resulting file here or to a later configuration file.

   * `brew-options.fs' Configuration file to change some
     initialisations done by `brew-defaults.fs' or `brew-init.fs'.

   * `my-brew-options.fs' Configuration file to put personal adaptions
     and preferences.




